1
00:01:13,260 --> 00:01:14,510
I warned you!

2
00:01:14,531 --> 00:01:17,569
Did I not warn you what would
come of dealing with Dwarves?

3
00:01:17,599 --> 00:01:18,950
Now they've done it!

4
00:01:18,990 --> 00:01:22,694
They've woken the dragon, they've
brought the apocalypse upon our heads.

5
00:01:22,724 --> 00:01:24,245
Come on, quickly, quickly.

6
00:01:24,305 --> 00:01:27,635
Faster now, I'm trying
to evacuate myself here.

7
00:01:27,685 --> 00:01:29,006
Careful with that.

8
00:01:29,045 --> 00:01:31,408
Never mind the books! Get
on, get the rest of it.

9
00:01:31,448 --> 00:01:33,646
But Sire, should we not
try to save the town?

10
00:01:33,676 --> 00:01:37,390
The town is lost, save the gold!

11
00:01:42,020 --> 00:01:43,151
Pile 'em up!

12
00:01:55,847 --> 00:01:58,947
We have no time, we must leave.
- Get him up.

13
00:01:58,986 --> 00:02:00,628
Come on, brother.
- Come on, come on, let's go.

14
00:02:00,668 --> 00:02:02,650
I'm fine, I can walk.
- As fast as you can.

15
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:05,668
We're not leaving, not
without our father.

16
00:02:05,698 --> 00:02:10,633
If you stay here, your sisters will die.
Is that what your father would want?

17
00:02:12,350 --> 00:02:16,795
Open this door. Do you hear me!

18
00:02:27,877 --> 00:02:29,549
Down here, now!

19
00:02:29,568 --> 00:02:31,490
Give me your hand.
- Come on, we gotta go!

20
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:33,401
Quickly now, hurry!

21
00:02:33,442 --> 00:02:35,093
Kíli, come on!

22
00:03:23,188 --> 00:03:24,759
Come on! Come On!

23
00:03:24,789 --> 00:03:27,301
Faster! Faster!

24
00:03:30,531 --> 00:03:31,662
If only we could take...

25
00:03:31,701 --> 00:03:34,524
more of these poor people with us.
But they're hardly...

26
00:03:34,555 --> 00:03:36,876
worth it. I quite agree.

27
00:03:43,819 --> 00:03:45,139
Look out!

28
00:03:51,081 --> 00:03:52,091
Move it.

29
00:03:52,132 --> 00:03:53,203
Move it!

30
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:55,632
Come on! Faster!

31
00:03:55,671 --> 00:03:57,663
My gold! My gold!

32
00:03:57,682 --> 00:03:58,663
We carry too much weight.

33
00:03:58,683 --> 00:04:00,335
We need to dump something.

34
00:04:00,354 --> 00:04:03,194
You gotta go, Alfrid.

35
00:04:10,276 --> 00:04:11,997
Faster! Faster!

36
00:05:27,536 --> 00:05:30,237
Poor souls.

37
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:51,600
Da!

38
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:53,829
Da!

39
00:06:57,973 --> 00:06:59,033
He hit it!

40
00:06:59,053 --> 00:07:01,062
- He hit the dragon!
- No.

41
00:07:01,091 --> 00:07:02,884
He did, he hit it's mark, I saw.

42
00:07:02,913 --> 00:07:05,125
These arrows can not
pierce it's hide.

43
00:07:05,185 --> 00:07:09,334
Actually, nothing will.

44
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:22,101
What are you doing?

45
00:07:22,132 --> 00:07:24,353
- Come back! Bain!
- Come back!

46
00:07:24,370 --> 00:07:25,721
Bain!

47
00:07:25,762 --> 00:07:27,233
- Come back here!
- Bain!

48
00:07:27,273 --> 00:07:28,374
Leave him!

49
00:07:28,403 --> 00:07:30,175
We cannot go back.

50
00:07:30,225 --> 00:07:31,276
Bain!

51
00:07:54,115 --> 00:07:55,115
Dad!

52
00:07:56,334 --> 00:07:58,334
Bain! What are you doing?
Why didn't you...

53
00:07:58,365 --> 00:07:59,505
leave, you were
supposed to leave.

54
00:07:59,526 --> 00:08:00,586
I came to help you.

55
00:08:00,637 --> 00:08:04,547
No, nothing can stop it now.
- This might.

56
00:08:08,180 --> 00:08:10,591
Bain, you go back.

57
00:08:10,641 --> 00:08:13,000
You get out of here now.

58
00:08:15,271 --> 00:08:16,273
Da!

59
00:08:21,843 --> 00:08:23,035
Bain!

60
00:08:23,095 --> 00:08:24,346
Da!

61
00:08:35,568 --> 00:08:36,769
Stop, stop! Halt,

62
00:08:36,820 --> 00:08:37,951
halt!

63
00:08:45,383 --> 00:08:49,186
Who are you that would stand...

64
00:08:49,235 --> 00:08:51,504
against me?

65
00:08:54,557 --> 00:08:59,378
Now that is a pity.

66
00:08:59,427 --> 00:09:04,111
What will you do now... bowman?

67
00:09:04,961 --> 00:09:07,591
You are forsaken.

68
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:11,374
No help will come.

69
00:09:12,514 --> 00:09:14,013
Now's our chance!

70
00:09:14,072 --> 00:09:14,903
Go now!

71
00:09:14,943 --> 00:09:17,546
Hit to the open water!

72
00:09:17,586 --> 00:09:23,376
Hmm... ahh! Is that your child?

73
00:09:25,099 --> 00:09:30,830
You cannot save him from the fire.
He will...

74
00:09:30,850 --> 00:09:33,351
burn!

75
00:09:51,330 --> 00:09:53,388
Stay still, son.

76
00:09:53,427 --> 00:09:55,389
Stay still.

77
00:09:56,510 --> 00:09:57,802
Tell me,

78
00:09:57,851 --> 00:10:03,682
wretch, how now shall
you challenge me?

79
00:10:08,453 --> 00:10:13,697
You have nothing
left but your...

80
00:10:13,717 --> 00:10:16,100
death!

81
00:10:19,188 --> 00:10:20,679
Bain. Look at me.

82
00:10:21,921 --> 00:10:23,201
You look at me.

83
00:10:27,812 --> 00:10:29,183
A little to your left.

84
00:10:31,306 --> 00:10:32,713
That's it.

85
00:10:48,590 --> 00:10:51,341
Bain! Hold on!

86
00:11:31,106 --> 00:11:34,956
Wh-what was that? What happened?

87
00:11:35,017 --> 00:11:37,158
It fell, I saw it.

88
00:11:40,081 --> 00:11:41,081
It's dead.

89
00:11:45,381 --> 00:11:46,793
Smaug is dead.

90
00:11:46,823 --> 00:11:51,014
By my beard, I think he's right!

91
00:11:51,073 --> 00:11:53,105
Look there!

92
00:11:53,134 --> 00:12:00,158
The Ravens of Erebor are
returning to the Mountain.

93
00:12:00,197 --> 00:12:03,000
Aye, word will spread.
Before long...

94
00:12:03,019 --> 00:12:09,402
every soul in Middle Earth
will know the Dragon is dead.

95
00:12:18,645 --> 00:12:24,567
_

96
00:12:45,965 --> 00:12:50,278
<i>You are not alone, Mithrandir.</i>

97
00:13:07,875 --> 00:13:10,554
<i>Will somebody help me!
Hey, let me go.</i>

98
00:13:10,605 --> 00:13:12,546
Help!

99
00:13:21,519 --> 00:13:23,818
- Da!
- Da!

100
00:13:23,849 --> 00:13:24,850
Da!

101
00:13:31,524 --> 00:13:33,693
Ahh! Why me?

102
00:13:42,386 --> 00:13:44,149
Tauriel.

103
00:13:45,219 --> 00:13:46,009
Kíli...

104
00:13:46,059 --> 00:13:47,557
come on.

105
00:13:47,597 --> 00:13:49,259
We're leaving.

106
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:51,640
They are your
people, you must...

107
00:13:51,691 --> 00:13:53,873
go.

108
00:13:53,903 --> 00:13:56,532
Come with me.

109
00:13:56,601 --> 00:13:58,974
I know how I feel,
I'm not afraid.

110
00:13:59,014 --> 00:14:00,644
You make me feel alive.

111
00:14:00,695 --> 00:14:01,475
No, I can't.

112
00:14:01,525 --> 00:14:03,374
Tauriel,

113
00:14:03,423 --> 00:14:05,196
amrâlimê.

114
00:14:09,769 --> 00:14:11,226
I don't know what that means.

115
00:14:13,139 --> 00:14:15,230
I think you do.

116
00:14:22,182 --> 00:14:23,884
_

117
00:14:27,014 --> 00:14:29,335
_

118
00:14:31,466 --> 00:14:32,817
_

119
00:14:59,326 --> 00:15:03,188
Keep it... as a promise.

120
00:15:30,838 --> 00:15:34,051
These are dry. You'll need them.
- Thank you.

121
00:15:34,091 --> 00:15:36,173
Oi, give me one of them!

122
00:15:36,212 --> 00:15:37,600
I'll catch my...

123
00:15:37,640 --> 00:15:40,243
death in this cold.
- Find your own!

124
00:15:40,263 --> 00:15:43,534
You're not in charge now, Alfrid
Lickspittle. - That is where you are wrong.

125
00:15:43,585 --> 00:15:45,594
In the absence of the Master...

126
00:15:45,624 --> 00:15:46,794
the powers seeds to his...

127
00:15:46,835 --> 00:15:49,076
deputy, which in this
instance is my good self.

128
00:15:49,106 --> 00:15:50,988
Now give me that blanket!

129
00:15:52,605 --> 00:15:54,086
Master's Deputy?

130
00:15:54,116 --> 00:15:57,299
Don't make me laugh.
You're a sneak thief,

131
00:15:57,340 --> 00:15:58,900
more like. I'll be dead...

132
00:15:58,941 --> 00:16:00,339
before I answer to
the likes of you.

133
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:03,371
Maybe that can be arranged.

134
00:16:07,184 --> 00:16:10,884
I wouldn't go turning on
your own, Alfrid. Not now.

135
00:16:16,605 --> 00:16:20,879
Da! - Come here. - You're alive!

136
00:16:20,908 --> 00:16:22,509
It's all right.

137
00:16:25,349 --> 00:16:27,770
<i>It was Bard. He killed the...</i>

138
00:16:27,801 --> 00:16:30,182
dragon. I saw it
with me own eyes.

139
00:16:30,212 --> 00:16:32,751
He brought the beast down.
Struck him...

140
00:16:32,792 --> 00:16:36,024
dead with a Black Arrow.

141
00:16:42,206 --> 00:16:44,567
You've saved us all, bless you.

142
00:16:46,996 --> 00:16:50,450
All hail to the Dragon-slayer!

143
00:16:50,509 --> 00:16:52,250
All hail...

144
00:16:52,290 --> 00:16:54,092
King Bard!

145
00:16:56,071 --> 00:17:01,355
I have said it many times,
this is a man of noble stock.

146
00:17:01,394 --> 00:17:04,193
A born leader.
- Do not call me that.

147
00:17:04,253 --> 00:17:05,375
I'm not the Master...

148
00:17:05,404 --> 00:17:09,478
of this town. Where is he?

149
00:17:09,498 --> 00:17:12,267
Where's the master?
- Half way down the Anduin,

150
00:17:12,307 --> 00:17:14,749
with all our coin,
I don't doubt.

151
00:17:14,769 --> 00:17:16,089
You would know.

152
00:17:16,119 --> 00:17:18,409
You helped him empty...

153
00:17:18,449 --> 00:17:20,851
- the treasury.
- No,

154
00:17:20,871 --> 00:17:21,932
I tried to stop him.

155
00:17:21,971 --> 00:17:23,093
<i>Liar! Thief!</i>

156
00:17:23,883 --> 00:17:27,053
<i>You're a mongrel.
- I begged, I pleaded,</i>

157
00:17:29,295 --> 00:17:31,836
I said: "Master...

158
00:17:31,896 --> 00:17:32,896
No!"

159
00:17:35,856 --> 00:17:37,708
Think of the children.

160
00:17:39,439 --> 00:17:41,958
Will nobody think
of the children?

161
00:17:42,769 --> 00:17:44,259
<i>Aargh. Hang him!</i>

162
00:17:44,941 --> 00:17:46,491
To the tree with him!

163
00:17:55,465 --> 00:17:56,516
Let him down!

164
00:17:56,557 --> 00:17:58,164
Let him go!

165
00:18:01,166 --> 00:18:02,738
Look around you!

166
00:18:03,749 --> 00:18:04,640
Have you not...

167
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:06,627
had your fill of death?

168
00:18:09,450 --> 00:18:11,122
Winter is upon us.

169
00:18:11,162 --> 00:18:17,313
We must look to our own, to
the sick and the helpless.

170
00:18:17,363 --> 00:18:19,865
Those who can stand,
tend to the wounded,

171
00:18:19,894 --> 00:18:21,653
and those who have
strength left, follow me.

172
00:18:21,673 --> 00:18:24,635
We must salvage what we can.
- And what then?

173
00:18:24,675 --> 00:18:25,676
What do we do then?

174
00:18:30,317 --> 00:18:32,028
We find shelter.

175
00:19:17,055 --> 00:19:18,777
Hello!

176
00:19:20,528 --> 00:19:21,969
Bombur?

177
00:19:22,910 --> 00:19:24,357
Bifur?

178
00:19:25,449 --> 00:19:26,970
Anybody?

179
00:19:34,232 --> 00:19:35,232
<i>Wait!</i>

180
00:19:36,003 --> 00:19:37,134
<i>Wait!</i>

181
00:19:37,164 --> 00:19:38,435
It's Bilbo. He's alive!

182
00:19:38,465 --> 00:19:40,273
Stop! Stop!

183
00:19:40,304 --> 00:19:41,625
<i>Stop!</i>

184
00:19:41,654 --> 00:19:44,778
You need to leave. We
all need to leave.

185
00:19:44,807 --> 00:19:46,538
We only just got here.

186
00:19:46,568 --> 00:19:48,627
I tried talking to him,
but he won't listen.

187
00:19:48,647 --> 00:19:50,578
Who do you mean, laddie?
- Thorin!

188
00:19:50,598 --> 00:19:53,611
Thorin. Thorin, he's been
down there for days.

189
00:19:53,671 --> 00:19:55,609
He doesn't sleep,
he barely eats.

190
00:19:55,630 --> 00:19:58,952
He's not been himself, not at all.
It's this...

191
00:19:58,972 --> 00:20:01,924
it's this place. I think
a sickness lies upon it.

192
00:20:01,954 --> 00:20:03,272
A sickness?

193
00:20:03,303 --> 00:20:06,404
What kind of sickness?

194
00:20:07,836 --> 00:20:09,156
Fíli?

195
00:20:09,196 --> 00:20:10,194
Fíli!

196
00:20:11,046 --> 00:20:12,446
Fíli!

197
00:20:42,468 --> 00:20:43,469
Gold.

198
00:20:46,361 --> 00:20:48,372
Gold beyond measure...

199
00:20:50,911 --> 00:20:52,492
beyond sorrow...

200
00:20:52,522 --> 00:20:55,115
and grieve.

201
00:21:01,086 --> 00:21:04,159
Behold... the great...

202
00:21:04,179 --> 00:21:08,328
treasure hoard of Thrór.

203
00:21:15,631 --> 00:21:16,811
Welcome...

204
00:21:16,832 --> 00:21:19,594
my sisters sons...

205
00:21:23,453 --> 00:21:25,846
to the Kingdom...

206
00:21:25,875 --> 00:21:27,887
of Erebor.

207
00:21:30,826 --> 00:21:32,528
Balin!

208
00:21:34,390 --> 00:21:35,891
Bofur!

209
00:21:35,921 --> 00:21:37,568
Kíli! Bifur!

210
00:21:41,612 --> 00:21:45,102
- Bombur!
- You're alive!

211
00:21:46,272 --> 00:21:48,815
- Any sign of it?
- Nothing here.

212
00:21:48,875 --> 00:21:51,076
- Nothing here.
- Keep searching!

213
00:21:51,106 --> 00:21:52,755
That jewel could be any...

214
00:21:52,775 --> 00:21:55,287
where.
- The Arkenstone is in these halls.

215
00:21:55,317 --> 00:21:57,759
Find it!
- You heard him, keep looking.

216
00:21:57,788 --> 00:21:59,926
All of you!

217
00:21:59,987 --> 00:22:01,409
No-one rests until it is...

218
00:22:01,439 --> 00:22:03,599
found!

219
00:22:33,121 --> 00:22:37,453
<i>I am almost tempted
to let you take it,</i>

220
00:22:37,503 --> 00:22:39,123
<i>if only...</i>

221
00:22:39,173 --> 00:22:41,153
<i>to see Oakenshield...</i>

222
00:22:41,193 --> 00:22:42,625
<i>suffer.</i>

223
00:22:43,816 --> 00:22:44,817
<i>Watch it...</i>

224
00:22:44,866 --> 00:22:46,545
destroy him.

225
00:22:46,575 --> 00:22:48,406
<i>Watch it corrupt...</i>

226
00:22:48,426 --> 00:22:50,667
<i>his heart...</i>

227
00:22:50,698 --> 00:22:53,269
and drive him mad.

228
00:23:26,540 --> 00:23:28,813
Take only what you need,

229
00:23:28,833 --> 00:23:34,854
we have a long march ahead.
- Where will you go?

230
00:23:34,923 --> 00:23:39,347
There is only one place.

231
00:23:39,387 --> 00:23:41,306
The Mountain?

232
00:23:41,355 --> 00:23:44,018
You are a genius, Sire.

233
00:23:44,048 --> 00:23:46,990
We can take refuge
inside the Mountain.

234
00:23:47,020 --> 00:23:50,539
It might smell a bit of dragon.
The women could clean it up.

235
00:23:50,599 --> 00:23:54,834
It will be safe and warm and
dry, and full of stores,

236
00:23:54,854 --> 00:23:57,323
bedding and clothing,

237
00:23:57,363 --> 00:23:59,243
your bit of gold.

238
00:24:00,914 --> 00:24:02,926
What gold is in that
Mountain, is cursed.

239
00:24:02,946 --> 00:24:05,306
We will take only what
was promised to us,

240
00:24:05,336 --> 00:24:07,007
only what we need to rebuild...

241
00:24:07,037 --> 00:24:09,358
our lives.

242
00:24:09,388 --> 00:24:11,830
Here, pull your weight.

243
00:24:11,881 --> 00:24:16,330
News of the death of Smaug will
have spread through the lands.

244
00:24:16,371 --> 00:24:17,791
Aye.

245
00:24:19,804 --> 00:24:24,114
Others will now look
to the Mountain...

246
00:24:24,153 --> 00:24:25,744
for it's wealth...

247
00:24:25,765 --> 00:24:29,035
or it's position.
- What is it you know?

248
00:24:30,246 --> 00:24:35,380
Nothing for certain. It's
what I fear may come.

249
00:24:46,853 --> 00:24:49,153
_

