01:43:05,637 --> 01:43:06,729
Kíli!

1090
01:43:11,729 --> 01:43:12,780
Kíli!

1091
01:43:13,890 --> 01:43:16,430
- Tauriel!
- Kíli.

1092
01:44:21,416 --> 01:44:22,516
No!

1093
01:44:33,099 --> 01:44:34,130
No.

1094
01:49:48,430 --> 01:49:49,872
Tauriel!

1095
01:54:30,859 --> 01:54:32,601
The eagles are coming.

1096
01:55:22,859 --> 01:55:23,859
Hey, Bilbo.

1097
01:55:23,909 --> 01:55:26,591
No, don't look. Don't move.
Lie still.

1098
01:55:27,573 --> 01:55:28,724
Ow.

1099
01:55:30,702 --> 01:55:33,564
I'm glad you're here.
- Shh, shh, shh, shh.

1100
01:55:34,625 --> 01:55:37,373
I wish to part from you in friendship.
- No,

1101
01:55:37,444 --> 01:55:39,055
you are not going
anywhere, Thorin,

1102
01:55:39,095 --> 01:55:41,537
you're going to live.

1103
01:55:41,608 --> 01:55:44,707
I would take back my words
and my deeds at the gate.

1104
01:55:46,018 --> 01:55:48,819
You did what only a
true friend would do.

1105
01:55:50,481 --> 01:55:51,481
Forgive me.

1106
01:55:54,091 --> 01:55:55,863
I was too blind to see.

1107
01:55:58,685 --> 01:56:04,345
I am so sorry that I have
led you into such peril.

1108
01:56:04,405 --> 01:56:07,469
No, I-I'm glad to have shared
in your perils, Thorin.

1109
01:56:07,519 --> 01:56:08,936
Each and every one of them.

1110
01:56:12,198 --> 01:56:17,260
It is far more than
any Baggins deserves.

1111
01:56:20,192 --> 01:56:24,202
Farewell, Master Burglar.

1112
01:56:24,252 --> 01:56:31,805
Go back to your books
and your armchair.

1113
01:56:31,845 --> 01:56:34,296
Plant your trees,

1114
01:56:34,346 --> 01:56:39,297
watch them grow.

1115
01:56:41,439 --> 01:56:45,783
If more people valued home...

1116
01:56:45,853 --> 01:56:48,421
above gold,

1117
01:56:48,492 --> 01:56:53,496
this world would be
a merrier place.

1118
01:56:56,085 --> 01:56:58,567
No. No, no, no, no. No,

1119
01:56:58,617 --> 01:56:59,898
Thorin!

1120
01:56:59,948 --> 01:57:01,908
Thorin, don't you dare...

1121
01:57:03,518 --> 01:57:05,238
Thorin?

1122
01:57:10,332 --> 01:57:13,421
Look, Thorin. Thorin, hold on.

1123
01:57:13,452 --> 01:57:14,403
You hold on,

1124
01:57:14,453 --> 01:57:16,083
you see, the Eagles...

1125
01:57:16,123 --> 01:57:19,024
the Eagles, the Eagles are here.

1126
01:57:19,054 --> 01:57:23,737
Thorin...

1127
01:57:23,777 --> 01:57:26,038
the Eagles...

1128
01:58:21,898 --> 01:58:25,871
I... can not go back.

1129
01:58:25,921 --> 01:58:28,689
Where will you go?

1130
01:58:28,729 --> 01:58:31,351
I do not know.

1131
01:58:31,421 --> 01:58:33,132
Go north.

1132
01:58:33,193 --> 01:58:36,802
Find the Dúnedain.

1133
01:58:36,853 --> 01:58:39,826
There is a young ranger amongst
them, you should meet him.

1134
01:58:41,796 --> 01:58:49,100
His father Arathorn was a good man.
His son might grow to be a great one.

1135
01:58:51,771 --> 01:58:52,890
What is his name?

1136
01:58:52,960 --> 01:59:00,962
He is known in the wild as Strider. His
true name you must discover for yourself.

1137
01:59:05,515 --> 01:59:10,167
Legolas, your mother loved you,

1138
01:59:12,599 --> 01:59:17,158
more than anyone,
more than life.

1139
01:59:52,113 --> 01:59:54,265
They want to bury him.

1140
01:59:56,234 --> 01:59:57,905
Yes.

1141
01:59:58,975 --> 02:00:04,948
If this is love, I
do not want it.

1142
02:00:05,007 --> 02:00:09,811
Take it from me, please?

1143
02:00:14,462 --> 02:00:17,333
Why does it hurt so much?

1144
02:00:17,384 --> 02:00:21,113
Because it was real.

1145
02:03:05,828 --> 02:03:11,569
There is to be a great feast tonight.
Songs will be sung, tales will be told,

1146
02:03:13,570 --> 02:03:15,671
and Thorin Oakenshield...

1147
02:03:15,712 --> 02:03:17,751
will pass into legend.

1148
02:03:19,271 --> 02:03:20,993
I know that's how you must...

1149
02:03:21,054 --> 02:03:24,225
honour him, but to me,
he was never that.

1150
02:03:24,286 --> 02:03:26,765
He was...

1151
02:03:26,824 --> 02:03:29,907
to me...

1152
02:03:29,947 --> 02:03:32,850
he was...

1153
02:03:38,461 --> 02:03:41,409
Well, I think I'll slip quietly away,
will you tell the others I said goodbye?

1154
02:03:41,470 --> 02:03:44,152
You can tell them yourself.

1155
02:03:59,717 --> 02:04:03,320
If any of you are ever
passing Bag-End...

1156
02:04:08,101 --> 02:04:09,542
tea is at four.

1157
02:04:11,154 --> 02:04:13,762
There's plenty of it...

1158
02:04:15,493 --> 02:04:17,265
and you are welcome any time.

1159
02:04:23,027 --> 02:04:24,398
Uh...

1160
02:04:26,029 --> 02:04:27,560
don't bother knocking.

1161
02:05:10,015 --> 02:05:12,296
Ahh, the borders of the...

1162
02:05:12,346 --> 02:05:14,007
Shire.

1163
02:05:14,047 --> 02:05:16,377
It is here I must leave you.

1164
02:05:18,639 --> 02:05:20,750
That's a shame.

1165
02:05:22,759 --> 02:05:24,340
I quite liked having a...

1166
02:05:24,380 --> 02:05:29,793
wizard around. It seems
they bring good luck.

1167
02:05:29,833 --> 02:05:32,052
You don't really
suppose, do you,

1168
02:05:32,092 --> 02:05:36,185
that all your adventures and
escapes were managed by mere luck.

1169
02:05:36,216 --> 02:05:40,686
Magic rings should not
be used lightly, Bilbo.

1170
02:05:40,747 --> 02:05:43,639
Don't take me for a fool, I
know you found one... - No.

1171
02:05:43,668 --> 02:05:46,859
In the Goblin tunnels, and
I've kept my eye on you...

1172
02:05:46,939 --> 02:05:48,520
ever since.

1173
02:05:51,462 --> 02:05:53,344
Well, thank goodness.

1174
02:05:57,743 --> 02:06:00,145
Farewell, Gandalf.

1175
02:06:02,043 --> 02:06:03,916
Farewell.

1176
02:06:10,877 --> 02:06:12,139
You uhh...

1177
02:06:12,168 --> 02:06:16,032
you needn't worry about that ring, it
fell out of my pocket during the battle.

1178
02:06:16,061 --> 02:06:18,201
I lost it.

1179
02:06:18,240 --> 02:06:23,454
You're a very fine person,
Mr Baggins, and I'm very...

1180
02:06:23,505 --> 02:06:25,823
fond of you.

1181
02:06:25,904 --> 02:06:33,029
But you're only quite a little
fellow in a wide world after all.

1182
02:07:04,291 --> 02:07:07,430
Wait a minute, that my
mother's glory box.

1183
02:07:07,470 --> 02:07:08,640
And that's...

1184
02:07:08,671 --> 02:07:10,091
my dining chair?

1185
02:07:10,122 --> 02:07:13,261
Hey, put that poof down!

1186
02:07:13,301 --> 02:07:15,193
What is going on?

1187
02:07:15,222 --> 02:07:16,163
Hello, mister...

1188
02:07:16,213 --> 02:07:19,176
Bilbo. You're not
supposed to be here.

1189
02:07:19,235 --> 02:07:21,074
What do you mean?

1190
02:07:21,125 --> 02:07:22,926
On account of you being
presumed dead and all.

1191
02:07:22,956 --> 02:07:28,438
I am not dead,
presumed or otherwise.

1192
02:07:28,467 --> 02:07:32,591
I'm not sure that's permitted.
Mister Bilbo!

1193
02:07:32,640 --> 02:07:36,980
<i>Anyone. Any bids on 21?
Any ones on 21?</i>

1194
02:07:37,051 --> 02:07:38,462
<i>Sold to Mrs. Bolder! ...
For sale, by auction, the</i>

1195
02:07:38,487 --> 02:07:40,006
effects and estate of... the Late Mr.
Bilbo Baggins...

1196
02:07:40,033 --> 02:07:43,382
Somewhere for Fatty
to put his feet on.

1197
02:07:44,663 --> 02:07:45,864
So do I have any bids...

1198
02:07:45,914 --> 02:07:48,476
for this. This is Shire-made.

1199
02:07:48,506 --> 02:07:51,765
None of your Dwarvish reproductions
here, honestly. - Stop!

1200
02:07:51,805 --> 02:07:54,569
Stop, there's been a mistake.

1201
02:07:54,599 --> 02:07:56,760
Who are you?
- What do you mean "who am I"?

1202
02:07:56,819 --> 02:07:58,511
You know perfectly
well who I am,

1203
02:07:58,572 --> 02:08:00,590
Lobelia Sackville Baggins.

1204
02:08:00,640 --> 02:08:02,220
This is my home...

1205
02:08:02,261 --> 02:08:05,033
and those are my spoons,
thank you very much.

1206
02:08:05,083 --> 02:08:07,682
This is most irregular.
It's been more...

1207
02:08:07,762 --> 02:08:10,255
than 13 months since
the disappearance.

1208
02:08:10,305 --> 02:08:12,145
If you are in fact...

1209
02:08:12,206 --> 02:08:15,426
Bilbo Baggins and undeceased?

1210
02:08:15,485 --> 02:08:17,167
Can you prove it?

1211
02:08:17,247 --> 02:08:18,247
What?

1212
02:08:18,268 --> 02:08:20,158
Well... uh, something
official...

1213
02:08:20,208 --> 02:08:22,717
with your name on it would suffice.
- All right.

1214
02:08:22,787 --> 02:08:23,838
Right!

1215
02:08:25,780 --> 02:08:28,792
A contract of employment as a

1216
02:08:28,842 --> 02:08:32,533
a but... Never mind that one.

1217
02:08:34,283 --> 02:08:38,234
There, my signature.
- Yes, well... uh...

1218
02:08:38,304 --> 02:08:43,557
o, it certainly seems to be in order.
Yes, it seems there can be no doubt.

1219
02:08:43,587 --> 02:08:46,688
Who is this person you
pledged your service to?

1220
02:08:48,099 --> 02:08:50,260
Thorin Oakenshield?

1221
02:08:53,662 --> 02:08:55,641
He...

1222
02:08:55,671 --> 02:08:58,873
he was my friend.

1223
02:10:52,105 --> 02:10:53,726
No, thank you!

1224
02:10:53,796 --> 02:10:58,747
We don't want any more visitors,
well-wishers, or distant relations!

1225
02:10:58,797 --> 02:10:59,939
And what about...

1226
02:10:59,998 --> 02:11:02,560
very old friends?

1227
02:11:09,453 --> 02:11:12,395
- Gandalf?
- Bilbo Baggins!

1228
02:11:12,435 --> 02:11:15,914
My dear Gandalf!
- It's good to see you.

1229
02:11:15,984 --> 02:11:20,578
One hundred and eleven years old.
Who would believe it?

1230
02:11:23,747 --> 02:11:26,000
Come on, come in.

1231
02:11:26,029 --> 02:11:28,671
Welcome, welcome.

